                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/143: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dye</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Tex</hi>
                        </placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-08T10:30:00-07:00"
                            >March 8, 1929—10:30 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Battle continues but rebels have taken nearly whole city of Juarez. Federals hold
                    only strip of territory along river bank. Rebels avoiding firing into American
                    territory though one known casualty here. General Ramos, commander Federals, has
                    just called for conference with Mexican Consul General, El Paso.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dye</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
